### =========================================================
### EVENTPRO CI - Tests API (extension VS Code "REST Client")
### Clique sur "Send Request" (apparait au-dessus de chaque bloc).
### Lance d'abord "Connexion (token)" : le token est reutilise
### automatiquement dans les requetes protegees.
### =========================================================

@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000

### 1) Inscription (register)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/register/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "nouveau_participant",
  "email": "nouveau@eventpro.ci",
  "password": "Test@2025",
  "role": "PARTICIPANT"
}

### 2) Connexion (token JWT)  -- lance CELLE-CI en premier
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/token/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "organisateur1",
  "password": "Orga@2025"
}

### 3) Rafraichir le token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/token/refresh/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh": "{{login.response.body.$.refresh}}"
}

### 4) Liste des evenements (public)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/

### 5) Creer un evenement (organisateur, protege par JWT)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access}}

{
  "title": "Concert de demonstration",
  "description": "Cree via l'API",
  "category": "CONCERT",
  "date": "2026-12-01T20:00:00Z",
  "end_date": "2026-12-01T23:00:00Z",
  "location": "Abidjan",
  "max_capacity": 200,
  "status": "PUBLISHED"
}

### 6) Detail d'un evenement
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/events/1/

### 7) Tableau de bord organisateur (protege)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/dashboard/
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access}}

### 8) Reserver un billet (protege) -- adapte ticket_type_id si besoin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/tickets/book/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.$.access}}

{
  "ticket_type_id": 1
}

### 9) [Permissions] Connexion en PARTICIPANT
# @name loginPart
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/token/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "participant1",
  "password": "Part@2025"
}

### 10) [Permissions] Un PARTICIPANT tente de creer un evenement -> DOIT ETRE REFUSE
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{loginPart.response.body.$.access}}

{
  "title": "Tentative interdite",
  "description": "Un participant ne peut pas creer d'evenement",
  "date": "2026-12-01T20:00:00Z",
  "location": "Abidjan",
  "max_capacity": 100
}

### 11) [Auth] Creer un evenement SANS token -> DOIT ETRE REFUSE (401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/events/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Sans authentification",
  "description": "Aucun token fourni",
  "date": "2026-12-01T20:00:00Z",
  "location": "Abidjan",
  "max_capacity": 100
}